==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Catalytic
<hw>Cat`a*ly"tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Relating to, or
causing, catalysis.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>catalytic</xex> power is ill
understood.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Ure.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Catalytic force</b></col>, <cd>that form of chemical
energy formerly supposed to determine catalysis.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Catalytic</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Catalytic
<hw>Cat`a*lyt"ic</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An agent
employed in catalysis, as platinum black, aluminium chloride,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>catalyze</ent>⟦br⟧
